import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='lat', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['lat'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['lat'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['lat'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['lat'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitude in the University District?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['lat'] = pd.to_numeric(data['lat'], errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x=data['lat'], ax=ax, color='lightblue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Latitude')
    ax.axvline(x=data['lat'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {data["lat"].mean():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average latitude of locations in the University District?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.countplot(x="key", data=data, color='blue')
    ax.axhline(y=0.2, color='red', linestyle='--', label='0.2')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of unique key values in the University District dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.boxplot(x=data['lat'], color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['lat'].min(), color='red', label=f"Min: {data['lat'].min():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(x=data['lat'].max(), color='green', label=f"Max: {data['lat'].max():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the range of latitude values in the University District dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
